        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 1 at 8:29AM PDT by NWS San Francisco CA</headline>
        <description>At 829 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from over Boulder Creek to 12 miles west of
Boulder Creek, or extending from 9 miles southwest of Saratoga to 20
miles northwest of Santa Cruz, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Santa Cruz, Scotts Valley, Ben Lomond, Boulder Creek, Felton and
Lexington Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
